<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="308" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,259,574]" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,295,321]" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Among all currently known females of the genus, 
<taxonomicName authority="Salgado &amp; Ruiz, 2020" authorityName="Salgado &amp; Ruiz" authorityYear="2020" box="[892,1004,295,321]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Marma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abaira" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[892,1004,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">M. abaira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1011,1101,295,321]" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1011,1101,295,321]" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1116,1199,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1856,1880]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,597,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-172@21.[151,1435,597,1832]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 18. Female holotype of Marma abaira sp. nov. (UFMG 15049). A–B habitus (A dorsal, B ventral). C–D cleared epigyne/vulva (C ventral, D dorsal).Abbreviations: BG—Bennett’s gland; cd—copulatory duct; co—copulatory opening; fd—fer- tilization duct; PS—Primary spermatheca; SS—secondary spermatheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4456889" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4456889/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">Figs 18</figureCitation>
C–D) is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1902" box="[182,281,331,357]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Marma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baeri">
<emphasis box="[182,281,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">M. baeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[299,387,331,358]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1503,1527]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-24@10.[151,1435,181,1480]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Female of Marma baeri Simon, 1902, specimen from Montañita/Santa Elena/Ecuador (QCAZ). A–B habitus (A dorsal, B ventral); C–D cleared epigyne/vulva (C ventral, cleared; D details of secondary spermathecae, dorsal). Abbreviations: BG—Bennett’s gland; cd—copulatory duct; co—copulatory opening; fd—fertilization duct; e—embolus shaft (broken inside the duct); PS—Primary spermatheca; SS—secondary spermathecae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4456849" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4456849/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">Fig. 6C</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Caporiacco" baseAuthorityYear="1955" box="[454,576,331,357]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Marma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="femella">
<emphasis box="[454,576,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">M. femella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the copulatory openings far from each other and the copulatory ducts not encircling the primary spermathecae (
<figureCitation box="[682,790,367,394]" captionStart="FIGURE 58" captionStartId="63.[151,250,1595,1619]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,271,1549]" captionTargetId="figure-41@63.[151,1435,237,1571]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="FIGURE 58. Epigyne/vulva, A–C, E–K ventral, D dorsal [A Marma baeri Simon, 1902; B M. linae sp. nov.; C M. abaira sp. nov.; D M. femella (Caporiacco, 1955); E M. pipa sp. nov.; F M. wesolowskae sp. nov.; G M. nigritarsis (Simon, 1900); H M. sinuosa sp. nov.; I M. argentina (Mello-Leitão, 1941); J M. rosea (Mello-Leitão, 1941); K M. spelunca sp. nov.]. Colors represent homologous structures; arrow in D shows hypothetical position of secondary spermatheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4456981" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4456981/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">Figs 58A</figureCitation>
, C–D). However, 
<taxonomicName authority="Salgado &amp; Ruiz, 2020" authorityName="Salgado &amp; Ruiz" authorityYear="2020" box="[993,1105,367,393]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Marma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abaira" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[993,1105,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">M. abaira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1112,1201,367,393]" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1112,1201,367,393]" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1902" box="[214,311,403,429]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Marma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baeri">
<emphasis box="[214,311,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">M. baeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having elliptical primary spermathecae (the proximal portion is dilated, and the distal portion is narrow in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1902" box="[267,364,439,465]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Marma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baeri">
<emphasis box="[267,364,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">M. baeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<figureCitation box="[379,470,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1503,1527]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-24@10.[151,1435,181,1480]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Female of Marma baeri Simon, 1902, specimen from Montañita/Santa Elena/Ecuador (QCAZ). A–B habitus (A dorsal, B ventral); C–D cleared epigyne/vulva (C ventral, cleared; D details of secondary spermathecae, dorsal). Abbreviations: BG—Bennett’s gland; cd—copulatory duct; co—copulatory opening; fd—fertilization duct; e—embolus shaft (broken inside the duct); PS—Primary spermatheca; SS—secondary spermathecae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4456849" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4456849/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">Figs 6C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[482,508,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1856,1880]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,597,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-172@21.[151,1435,597,1832]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 18. Female holotype of Marma abaira sp. nov. (UFMG 15049). A–B habitus (A dorsal, B ventral). C–D cleared epigyne/vulva (C ventral, D dorsal).Abbreviations: BG—Bennett’s gland; cd—copulatory duct; co—copulatory opening; fd—fer- tilization duct; PS—Primary spermatheca; SS—secondary spermatheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4456889" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4456889/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">18</figureCitation>
C–D, 58A, C) and by having copulatory openings closest to each other (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 58" captionStartId="63.[151,250,1595,1619]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,271,1549]" captionTargetId="figure-41@63.[151,1435,237,1571]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="FIGURE 58. Epigyne/vulva, A–C, E–K ventral, D dorsal [A Marma baeri Simon, 1902; B M. linae sp. nov.; C M. abaira sp. nov.; D M. femella (Caporiacco, 1955); E M. pipa sp. nov.; F M. wesolowskae sp. nov.; G M. nigritarsis (Simon, 1900); H M. sinuosa sp. nov.; I M. argentina (Mello-Leitão, 1941); J M. rosea (Mello-Leitão, 1941); K M. spelunca sp. nov.]. Colors represent homologous structures; arrow in D shows hypothetical position of secondary spermatheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4456981" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4456981/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">Figs 58A, C</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="Salgado &amp; Ruiz, 2020" authorityName="Salgado &amp; Ruiz" authorityYear="2020" box="[194,360,475,501]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Marma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abaira" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[194,360,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">Marma abaira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[368,459,475,501]" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[368,459,475,501]" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Caporiacco" baseAuthorityYear="1955" box="[768,889,475,501]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Marma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="femella">
<emphasis box="[768,889,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">M. femella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the copulatory openings placed more anteriorly, and the primary spermathecae projecting to the anterior side (laterally projecting in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Caporiacco" baseAuthorityYear="1955" box="[1248,1370,511,537]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Marma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="femella">
<emphasis box="[1248,1370,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">M. femella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1856,1880]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,597,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-172@21.[151,1435,597,1832]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 18. Female holotype of Marma abaira sp. nov. (UFMG 15049). A–B habitus (A dorsal, B ventral). C–D cleared epigyne/vulva (C ventral, D dorsal).Abbreviations: BG—Bennett’s gland; cd—copulatory duct; co—copulatory opening; fd—fer- tilization duct; PS—Primary spermatheca; SS—secondary spermatheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4456889" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4456889/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">Figs 18</figureCitation>
C–D, 58C–D). Male unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
